==Starting off==
* ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Yarr! What will it be?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Let's see what you have.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Any word from Old Grog?}}
* {{topt|Got any work that needs doing here?}}
** '''Player:''' Got any work that needs doing here?
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Well, it just so happens that I'm looking for a rough, tough, piratical type for an adventure on the high seas!
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' And I'm happy to say...
** {{tcond|If the player does not meet the requirements for Prying Times:}}
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' ... it isn't you!
*** {{tbox|You do not meet all of the requirements to start the Prying Times miniquest.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' ... it is you!
** {{tcond|If the player's recommended combat is lower than 10:}}
*** {{tbox|Before starting this miniquest, be aware that your combat level is lower than the recommended level of 10.}}
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tselect|Start the Prying Times miniquest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Great! So what do you need?
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Hoist your mast, [player name], because there's some pirate looty just begging to be uncovered in a far off land! Thanks to me, you could be one of the privileged few to get your hands on it!
*** '''Player:''' Looty? You mean treasure?
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Yarr!
*** '''Player:''' Well, I can't say no to a bit of treasure. What do I need to do?
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Shiver me timbers! There is a crate full of high value goods just sitting at the port of Sarim!
*** '''Player:''' Port Sarim? I thought you said far off land?
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Aye! The far off land of Sarim!
*** '''Player:''' Okay... but surely if this is pirate treasure, someone would have noticed... Port Sarim is a busy place.
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Luckily for us, a cunning Jolly Roger of a pirate has disguised it to look like a normal crate of cargo!
*** '''Player:''' Hang on... is this actually just a normal cargo delivery? You know there's a notice board on the docks for that sort of thing...
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Normal?! Normal?! What kind of scallywag are you? There's nothing normal about a valuable crate of precious plundered pirate looty!
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Besides, you've already said you'll do it, and pirates never go back on their word.
*** '''Player:''' I'm fairly certain they do, but fine. I'll go collect this crate for you.
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Me hearty goes out to you! Once you have the looty, just leave it with the port master here. Now, give me your log and I'll write out the details.
*** {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the log:}}
**** '''Player:''' I'm afraid I don't have it on me.
**** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Well, go get it sailor! Heave to!
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{tcond|If the player has max port tasks taken:}}
**** {{tbox|pic=Captain's log  detail.png|You hand your log to Steve and he flicks through the pages. After a moment, he hands it back without writing anything in it.}}
**** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Bit of a problem, I'm afraid! It seems your log is already full! You should get some of this work done before you take on my critical pirate task!
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Captain's log detail.png|You hand your log to Steve and he updates it with details on his request.}}
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Now, get to it, sailor! Heave to and ballast your grog!
*** {{mes|You have accepted the {{colour|teal|Pandemonium pirate looty delivery}} port task.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I've changed my mind. Maybe another time.
*** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Shiver me timbers!
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Could you tell me about the Pandemonium's one rule?}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Nothing, thanks.}}

