===Talking to 'Squawking' Steve Beanie===
* ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Yarr! What will it be?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Let's see what you have.}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Any word from Old Grog?}}
* {{topt|I delivered that cargo for you.}}
** '''Player:''' I delivered that cargo for you.
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Shiver me timbers! That was fast!
** '''Player:''' So could I have some 'looty' now?
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Blistering barnacles! You thought that was it? You are too funny, fellow sailor!
** '''Player:''' I get the feeling you're about to ask me to do something else...
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' Aye! This is no ordinary crate, [player name]. This is a pirate crate! Only a special key can open it for us!
** '''Player:''' But it is an ordinary crate, Steve. There was even a label on it addressed to you.
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' I hope you're not trying to call Squawking Steve Beanie a liar?! That crate is pirate looty, and anything suggesting otherwise is clearly a plot by my rival pirate captains!
** '''Player:''' Right... So what's this special key then?
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' It is something very few can forge! I suspect we will require the help of a master scallywag smith!
** '''Player:''' Is it essential that they be a scallywag as well as a smith? If not, I know of a dwarf near Mudskipper Point who might be able to help us.
** ''''Squawking' Steve Beanie:''' A dwarf? Yarr! That's an acceptable compromise! Ready your port side and go see this dwarf!
** '''Player:''' Okay, I'll grab a redberry pie and go visit Thurgo...
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Could you tell me about the Pandemonium's one rule?}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Nothing, thanks.}}

